	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Just a comment on the aforementioned combos using snare:  After getting your first DoT spell, go to Oasis.  Cast the following spells, in order:<BR>
1) Snare<BR>
2) Panic Animal (Terrorize?)<BR>
3) Stinging Swarm<BR>
<BR>
The animal runs slow, you can beat on it, it won't attack you, AND the DoT does full damage, even though the MOB is running! How?  The monster is in &quot;flee&quot; mode, and the &quot;nerf&quot; on DoTs to reduce kiting does not apply when the MOB is in this mode.  I listed Oasis as the place to go, because at level 14 I could solo a yellow/croc easily, with only the use of about 3/4 of my mana.<BR>
<BR>
Good luck to you all.<BR>
Danalen of Xegony
				</font>
			</td>

